<subsection xml:id="subsec-Constructing-angle-120">
        <title>Constructing <m>\angle 120^\circ</m></title>
        <activity>
            <statement>
                <p>
                Work in pairs  
                </p>

                <p>
                What  you need: A ruler, a protractor and a pair of compasses.
               </p>

                <p>
                    Explore.
                </p>

                <p>
                    1.Draw a line  and mark a point <m>O</m> on it.
                </p>

                    <image source="/l8.png " width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                <p>
                    2.With <m>O</m> as center draw an arc of any radius to cut the line  at <m>A</m>.
                </p>

                    <image source="/l9.png" width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                <p>
                    3.With same radius and with <m>A</m> as center draw another arc to cut the previous arc at <m>B</m>. With <m>B</m> as center draw another arc of same radius to cut the first arc at <m>C</m>.
                </p>

                    <image source="/l10.png" width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                <p>
                    4.Join <m>OC</m>. We get the required angle <me>\angle AOC = 120^\circ</me>.
                </p>

                    <image source="/l11.png" width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>
            </statement>
        </activity>

        <exercise>
             <figure>
                  <interactive xml:id="geogebra-constucting-angles-using-protractor" geogebra="hdhq7car" width="100%" aspect="9:5" reset-icon="yes" />
            </figure>
        </exercise>

    </subsection>

